definition.value: Any steroid ester based on an androstane skeleton.
A 2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl group is specified as tertadecanoyl (myristoyl).
A lysophosphatidylcholine 18:1 in which the acyl group is located at position 1.
A lysophosphatidylcholine 18:1 in which the acyl group is located at position 2.
A lysophosphatidylcholine 18:3 in which the acyl group is located at position 1.
A lysophosphatidylcholine 18:3 in which the acyl group is located at position 2.
A 2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the acyl group is specified as hexadecanoyl (palmitoyl).
A lysophosphatidylethanolamine 18:2 in which the acyl group is located at position 1.
A lysophosphatidylethanolamine 18:2 in which the acyl group is located at position 2.
Any seco-steroid based on a pregnane skeleton.
Any steroid ester based on a lanostane skeleton.
Any steroid ester based on a ergostane skeleton.
A tetrol that is 2-aminoicosane with the four hydroxy substituents located at position 1, 3, 4 and 5.
A tetrol that is 2-aminotetradecane with the theree hydroxy substituents located at position 1, 3, and 4.
An aminopyrimidine that is 5-methylpyrimidine-2,4-diamine in which one of the hydrogens of the methyl group has been replaced by a 2-cyclopropyl-7,8-dimethoxy-2H-chromen-5-yl group.
A 5-[(2-cyclopropyl-7,8-dimethoxy-2H-chromen-5-yl)methyl]pyrimidine-2,4-diamine in which the chiral centre has R configuration.
A 5-[(2-cyclopropyl-7,8-dimethoxy-2H-chromen-5-yl)methyl]pyrimidine-2,4-diamine in which the chiral centre has S configuration.
A flavone C-glycoside that consists of apigenin carrying alpha-L-arabinosyl and beta-L-arabinosyl groups at positions 6 and 8 respectively
A flavone C-glycoside that is apigenin carrying one or more pentosyl substituents.
A 1,2,4-oxadizole in which the hydrogens at positions 3 and 5 have been replaced by phenyl and thiophen-2-yl groups, respectively. It is used as a broad spectrum nematicidal seed treatment.
A flavone C-glycoside that consists of chrysoeriol carrying alpha-L-arabinosyl and beta-L-arabinosyl groups at positions 6 and 8 respectively
A cytidine 5'-phosphate obtained by formal condensation of the phosphate group of CMP with the phosphono group of phosphonoformic acid.
A tertiary amine oxide resulting from the formal oxidation of the amino group of dodecyldimethylamine.

A sulfonamide that is aminomethanesulfonic acid in which a hydrogen attached to the carbon has been replaced by a 1,5-dimethyl-3-oxo-2-phenyl-2,3-dihydro-1H-pyrazol-4-yl group and in which a hydrogen attached to the amino group has been replaced by a p-[(6-methoxypyridazin-3-yl)sulfamoyl]phenyl group.
A (1,5-dimethyl-3-oxo-2-phenyl-2,3-dihydro-1H-pyrazol-4-yl){4-[(6-methoxypyridazin-3-yl)sulfamoyl]anilino}methanesulfonic acid that has R configuration at the chiral centre.
A (1,5-dimethyl-3-oxo-2-phenyl-2,3-dihydro-1H-pyrazol-4-yl){4-[(6-methoxypyridazin-3-yl)sulfamoyl]anilino}methanesulfonic acid that has S configuration at the chiral centre.
An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the triphosphate OH groups of (8S)-3',8-cyclo-7,8-dihydroguanosine 5'-triphosphate; major species at pH 7.3.
An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of D-erythrulose 1-phosphate; major species at pH 7.3.
A glycosyloxyflavone that is  3',5'-di-O-methyltricetin (tricin) having a 6-O-malonyl-beta-D-glucosyl residue attached at the 7-hydroxy position
A dihydroxyflavone that is tricin 4'-O-(erythro-beta-guaiacylglyceryl) ether in which the hydroxy hydrogen at position 7'' has been replaced by a beta-D-glucopyranosyl group.

A EC 3.6.3.* (acid anhydride hydrolase catalysing transmembrane movement of substances) inhibitor that interferes with the action of channel-conductance-controlling ATPase (EC 3.6.3.49, also known as cystic fibrosis conductance regulator, CFCR).
Any steroid acid based on a lanostane skeleton.
A dihydroxyflavone that is tricin 4'-O-(erythro-beta-guaiacylglyceryl) ether in which the hydroxy hydrogen at position 9'' has been replaced by a beta-D-glucopyranosyl group.
A dihydroxyflavone that is tricin 4'-O-(threo-beta-guaiacylglyceryl) ether in which the phenolic hydrogen at position 7 has been replaced by a beta-D-glucopyranosyl group.
A glycosyloxyflavone that is  3',5'-di-O-methyltricetin (tricin) in which the phenolic hydrogen at position 5 has been replaced by a beta-D-glucopyranosyl group.
A glycosyloxyflavone that is 3',5'-di-O-methyltricetin (tricin) in which the phenolic hydrogen at position 7 has been replaced by a beta-D-glucopyranosyl group.
A glycosyloxyflavone that is 3',5'-di-O-methyltricetin (tricin) in which the phenolic hydrogen at position 7 has been replaced by a neohesperidosyl group.
An indolecarboxylic acid in which the carboxy group is the only substituent and is located at position 5.
A tetrahydroxyflavone that consists of isoorientin having a beta-glucosyl residue attached at position 2''.
An acyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of 2-hydroxyisobutanoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3

A vibsane diterpenoid that is (2Z,6E,10E)-cycloundeca-2,6,10-trien-1-one which is substituted at positions 2, 5, 5, 8, 9, and 9 by hydroxymethyl, methyl, 2-methylpent-2-en-5-yl, 3-methylbut-2-enoyloxy, hydroxy, and methyl groups, respectively (the 5S,8R,9R stereoisomer). It has been found to inhibit root growth in rice seedlings (IC50 0.14 mM).
Any deterpenoid whose with a structure that is characteristically found in the Viburnum species.
A (2S)-2-hydroxy monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of indolmycenic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
An organic heteropentacyclic compound that is isolated from the marine sponge Xestospongia exigua.

A 1,4-benzodiazepinone that is nordazepam in which the phenyl substituent has been replaced by a 1H-pyrrol-2-yl group. It inhibits gene expression in HIV-1 at the transcriptional level through interference with Tat-mediated transactivation.
An antagonist that binds to and deactivates the dopamine receptor D2, the main receptor for all antipsychotic drugs.
A member of the class of indoles that is tryptamine in which one of the amino hydrogens is replaced by an acetyl group while the hydrogen at position 2 is replaced by a benzyl group.
